by sanddbox on Sat Jan 01, 2011 9:35 pm	([msg=51496]see Re: my thought on right wrong[/msg])
What you are referring to, Orpheus, is the idea of Moral Relativism. The idea of moral relativity is gained in one of the later stages of moral development. That being said, the idea itself is not unique or groundbreaking - it's actually quite obvious, which is why this thread makes me meh a little bit. Instead of just stating the ideas of moral relativity, why not have an interesting discussion on it?I'd also probably be a bit more open to this thread if your entire post was not an explosion of grammatical failure.
